,Recommended,235380,17038426,"Posted: 13 July, 2015",all,Tela Vasir,"This is a quite interesting project so far and it's going to be even more promising in the future.Pros:- Two big modes are sure to make it into the release build: Singleplayer Campaign Mode (somewhat close to the BI classical campaigns) and Multiplayer Campaign (imagine a Clash of Clans in WWII setting... without constant donations reminder and the urge to watch the progress of your base each few hours).- Classical isometric view on warm and homey 2,5D graphics. Just like the old times, but with better effects.- Rock, Paper, Scissors gameplay in a whole - vehicles are good at destroying defences, infantry has something for everyone (apart from defences), and defences/obstacles when put in place can cripple any advancing enemy.- Developers are listening to the community, setting the highest priority to bug hunting and making the most wanted features come out first.- Great oldschool music, artwork, map decorations (some - with borderline humour)... You'll like it when you notice it :)Contras:- It's not BI as I thought it would be. Don't get me wrong - It's a fun game to play, but it's just not Blitzkrieg I. Not yet.- BIII is kinda poorly balanced on higher, advanced levels. I believe it will be fixed soon, but atm t5+ of the headquarters can be pain (imagine fighting Pershings with your KV-1s).- It's still Early Access. Expect to have some minor pathfinding bugs (I've met no other).Overall result?I'd say it's 7/10 for old Blitzkrieg players, 8/10 for Clash of Clans players and 9/10 for those dissapointed in Company of Heroes 2 fantasy-like setting (such as myself).Update 11.24.2015Game has surely evolved a lot since the last time I've launched it in the September. All sorts of improvements are here and ready to go:1. Pathfinding got fixed in a small unit groups. Yes, tactical combat still requires a lot of micromanaging but hey, it's what the Blitzkrieg series was about since like forefer.2. Developers really DO listen to the Community. All of the suggestions I've made as a regular Community member were answered to. Some made it into the game (like treating fortifications as if those were units in the means of a balance).3. Generals provide a unique experience with each and every faction. You can customize both your army now and the defences of your base like you see fit.4. Most balance issues are now gone, whilst 'Sauron's eye' should be fixed IMAO. It is a little bit too much OP.5. Numerous UI improvements here and there finally made the game easy to navigate.6. Should be first, actually... Now you can switch maps in Multiplayer Campaign. Yes. You can."
