76561198263380562,Recommended,235380,32556463,Posted: 18 June,all,Fluffiest Tank,"This game is quite decent for a completely different iteration of the Blitzkrieg franchise. I've played through the first two a while back, and I honestly don't see any problem with this one. In fact, I feel like this game in particular offers more replayability compared to the previous two games because of its sandbox-like elements (There isn't an actual ending). That and the achievement of getting 1,000 units being a thing. Now, it isn't perfect, but it is by no means a bad game. In fact, with some additional fixes and patches implemented, it could be an even more impressive game to play.As for those who have complained about the gameplay, I will have to just say that you just might be doing it wrong. The most common thing I hear is that ""infantry is useless"". I can assure you that you are not using them correctly, because infantry can be quite formidable when used properly. Anti-tank infantry are some of the most vindictive ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s I've come across (particularly the Russian ATR teams) that can ruin your tank force if you aren't careful or let them get too close. Assault infantry can soak up a lot of damage and can dish out just as much in return, and MG teams can suppress enemy infantry, which is something very few tanks can do (current exception being the A9 Cruiser Mk.I). Light vehicles have different purposes, be it anti-aircraft duties or reconnaissance, and tanks and tank destroyers are quite usefull for certain situations. Also, a tip for those who are failing to use infantry to their fullest potential would be to use cover such as buildings, trenches, and emplacements to enhance effectiveness and their chances of survival.My only complaint is with the Barbed wire and tank traps. I have over 15 hedgehogs in my inventory and the most you can put down is usually eight altogether. With that said, I'd like to see if the devs would implement a limit on how many mines and obstacles you can have. Otherwise I'll be staring at my screen contemplating why I have over 200 AT mines that I can't even place down. (Exaggeration is fun)Overall, I enjoy this game a lot. It might not be for everyone, but it is still a game that many will enjoy playing if they give it some time. It's not going to be like Men of War or Company of heroes, but in the end the payoff is worth it in my book."
