,Not Recommended,235380,24114454,"Posted: 5 July, 2016",all,Beetlelord,"Avoid this for now. This game is so bad right now after nearly a decade of writing perhaps 1 Steam review, I've found this so bad that it warrants a negative review.Major issues:♥♥♥♥♥♥ pathfindingBattles that take way too long and and are way too short (I will elaborate later)♥♥♥♥♥♥ difficulty curveSo the pathfinding. You have to manually, individually command units. If you do a big move order units get stuck, they get jammed and the best part is, if two units get stuck on each other they do damage! Brilliant game design choice there. It makes the most basic of features tiresome - moving your armies about.Units get vaporised in seconds if you're not careful. The ""artillery"" (Including planes, hence the quotation marks) is incredibly overuses by the AI and will wipe your entire army if you do not react in time. Currently I have no AA vehicles and I have no idea if they are even in the game. You have defensive AA but that's only for base defense. So it's a tiring slog through a basic mission, meaning the whole thing becomes an over-extended bore. You have to carefully, slowly poke forward and with the pathfinding being so bad even that can fail miserably to stop you getting hideously punished.So battles can and do end VERY quickly, often unfairly so.Now why do they take too long? If you manage to somehow best the above, you have to take down the HQ and their radar (it calls for ENDLESS reinforcements from the AI - seemingly) meaning the longer you take the MORE enemy units there are. What a catastrophically♥♥♥♥♥♥design flaw - punish people for moving too fast, punish people for moving too slow. So battles are both too slow and too fast. There's no happy medium and the game becomes a chore.Seriously, you can even check the ingame bars - it shows your unit score in blue. I start with nearly 600. They slowly die off, so does the enemies. Then BAM the enemy counter goes from 60 back to 600. Yet I have nothing now to counter?♥♥♥♥♥♥game design 101.So you think to rush the radar? Bad idea. The enemy reinforcements spawn in the HQ, it's cluttered so bad pathing becomes even more painful and the way LoS works means they will be able to snipe you from the Fog of War with impunity. Another exercise in frustration.So yeah.♥♥♥♥♥♥pathfinding,♥♥♥♥♥♥game design choices and a terribly balanced AI opponent have turned me so off this game it upsets me greatly. Avoid."
