76561198046190215,Not Recommended,235380,29066672,Posted: 6 January,all,Ashmole,"Needs more work.I was a big fan of Blitzkrieg 2 when it came out in the mid 2000's. So far, this game was a bit of a dissapointment for me.Issues- Not enough people playing online. I waited a very long time during multiple timeslots throughout the day adn wasn't able to get a match. I think the matchmaking system is based on your single player progress since I wasn't able to access the ""tier 3"" technology and wasn't able to match with people who had that tier unlocked.- Singleplayer is incredibly difficult. The singleplayer relies on you using your own units. This is problematic since you don't start out with many types of units and there is a cap on what you can use. There's no chance for reinforcements unless you have additional units in your queue. This made the first levels very difficult to play.- The interface needs some work. I discovered the multiplayer button (titled ""Frontline"") on the main map by accident. It didn't give any indication of what this button did until I clicked on it. The units in the game pop up icons when something happens to them but there is no way to decipher these icons.- Blitzkrieg 2 had a nice unit stats window that would appear on the main UI when you clicked the unit. This showed the gun's penetration capabilities, the armor, the HP, and how much damage the gun can do. This one just tells you the armor on the vehicle: it's less intuitive than B2's.- Performance is subpar considering the graphics quality and the fact that this is a RTS. I encountered lag quite frequently during the singleplayer despite having a GTX 970 and an I5.I think the ""clash of clans"" style base assault multiplayer has potential. I will be checking this game out in a future release, but right now I'm not ready for it."
