,Recommended,235380,32166830,Posted: 3 June,all,Ominous Cricket,"I have found Blitzkrieg III to be very enjoyable. The way they implement Line of Sight in this game, where every unit has a different view range instead of a universal range, is very fun to play with. Whether you use snipers to creep up on an enemy bunker for artillery to hammer, or scout cars to reveal an armor column on the road ahead, you will find it to be a satisfying mechanic to use once you understand it. Infantry in the first era seem weak, however this is because their weakest point is in the beginning of the game. Once you get a few upgrades, and learn how to make them hit the dirt and use cover, they start to last much longer and become valuable assets. This is a difficult game to understand and become good at. This is a game that rewards the player who uses ALL of their resources, and instills a feeling of accomplishment to those who plan and think through their strategies.I have never felt more accomplished when Ive beaten a mission or other player in any other game. Because, this game rewards the player who takes care of their forces, and utillizes everything handed to them.Anyways sorry for the wall of text, I really enjoy playing this game and I look forward to what the devs have planned for its bright future. Dont let those angry reviews deter you, try it out yourself. Play every nation, experience their playstyles and histories. Get lost in a very good simulation of World War II, from the first conflict, to the last."
