76561198133257200,Recommended,235380,15734718,"Posted: 7 May, 2015",all,Orion Nebula,"RTS for grown-ups is how I would summarize it.I bought this game when it came out, a few years ago, and it was interesting as an asymmetric multiplayer base attack and defense game.Still has that, but wow they added quite a lot of other stuff.Campaign for each of 3 factions, through early, mid, and late war. You build your army by collecting units after winning battles, and they keep their experience and level up over time, getting a little bit better.A skirmish mode against AI that is fairly challenging, but only a capture the flag control point type setup currently - no to the last man kind of battles, but it works well and keeps the games from getting too long and drawn out in this style. Boris is pretty good, can pop up with some surprises and a bear on harder difficulty.Multiplayer custom games, which I don't play, so don't have anything to say about the experience.So much to do in this, you can get lost with which to work on. Setting up base defenses, each unique for the 3 war periods, so 9 total if you hit tier 3 for each faction. Replaying the campaign missions to hit all the accomplishments, or just grinding for better war gear and legendary units you are missing.Etc...This game could easily keep you entertained for 500+ hours, assuming you are looking  for this kind of rts. Hopefully more people are and will wander in here and find this gem of a game, and play it long enough to see what it has to offer.Great job devs, I'd love to see some  modding support to add custom missions and stuff like that, but man I'm already over 100 hours and still messing with things that I haven't touched yet. RTS done well, they took many creative design ideas and stuck 'em out there. I for one appreciate that alone and am really enjoying the game!bye!"
